HEADWORD: Constantly
<hw>Con"stant*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>With constancy;
steadily; continually; perseveringly; without cessation;
uniformly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But she <qex>constantly</qex> affirmed that it was even so.</q>
<rj><qau>Acts. xii. 15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

